}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid7819457\charrsid16072257 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7819457 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Can you tell me how many years you lived in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I think it must have only been about - five years. Yes. Because my father moved his position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Which was the house you lived in longest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - oh, we must have lived in Moston Lane the longest, when I would be about - I think it would be when I was about nin
e or ten went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Can you tell me why you moved houses so often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Because of me father's position. He was a clerk and he worked for Conolly - for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Thorps}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  when they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
, Isaac Thorps in High Street and then - Conolly's the - oh cable people in Bleckley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 He was always a clerk was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Clerk, yes, and then he went to the Corporation tramways, which they called Dan Boyles railway at the time and he was there - Dan Boyles railway. Yes, because they would have all the Irishmen that the other people didn't want. Yes. And - he was a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 cashier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 there. Well he had to work shift work because of course the trams used to run all night so he left - after a while he left there and went to the L.N.Y. on Thorp Road Newton Heath as a clerk and was 
there - we went to live on Lightbowne Road whilst he worked there and then eventually rather than - it suited us better for the family to live at Redean Avenue Newton Heath and we lived there until he retired. And then they bought a house at Wildc-oft ave
nue Moston and - he died in - my mother died in 1940 and me father in 1943.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where did your father come from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 My father came from - he was born in Holland Street, Ancoats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where did your mother come from, was she a Manchester }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - she came - she must have come - I think she lived in Carruthers Street. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your father have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, my mother never went to work once she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your father have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No
, but he used to sing. Ah well - he used to - he was a singer and he sung at the Blackley Co-op hall and he's even sung at the Free Trade Hall at one time or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever make music as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - my - and my sisters sang and - as 
my father - I can't just remember the dates I have it somewhere where he belonged to the Moston Conservative Club and they made him a life member and we gave a concert - the family gave a concert. The my two sisters and their boyfriends and my brother and
 the younger brother sold programmes and of course I didn't do anything there, you know what I mean, I was the - I was never musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever sing together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. Yes, we had to do, we sang the hymns and everything at home and 
we - and we used to have Sunday evenings when anyone would come, family evenings and until of course Madge got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 the house was full of company on a Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have a lot of people visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, on a Sunday night we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did they come for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh well they'd come and they'd just have a bit of supper that's all, you know, sandwiches and a drink of tea or a drink of mineral but there was never any drink in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you go visiting other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, 
because you needed someone, you couldn't be complete. You had, each child as you grew older, you had a friend of your own and they sort of - well, one of them could perhaps play, I used to be able to play the piano but - sometimes there's too many there o
n the telegraph pole there was too many dots on the lines so - it got beyond me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go visiting people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, we used to go - we all used to go for Christmas to grandma's, back to Carruthers Street. Me father used to take us all and -
 we took side of a tram up, we used to have to walk up Blackley New Road to the tram shed which was opposite the-Farmyard Hotel and we used to get on the tram there and - coming home. Used to go to grandma's and we might have been the best children in the
 
world, our Edward's children she used to say about me father and - then we'd have our tea there, then of course set off for home and he used to take us in a place in - Swan Street, I think it was called McKenna's Vaults and I remember him - him having a d
rink and they gave us something in a glass and we had those you know, sort of shaker things to shake the sugar down, I don't know what it was we had but it was a treat. That was a treat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When your mother was ill did anybody help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, yes
, we had a - a lady in - she lived in Victoria Street, Mrs Garvie and she minded my mother over all the children. Yes. And when mother was in bed - well when me - me mother wasn't about, their eldest daughter Lizzie, would come and see to our meals and he
r mother did the washing and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have help from relatives at all, did you have relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh we had a grandma that made all our clothes. Yes. And she was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have relatives living nearby at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well then - they wanted me - my uncle and aunt wanted to take me because my mother was - had got this other baby, the new baby when we were in Blackley and - I went to their house and I wouldn't settle, so he had to walk from Beswick, from Quay Wes
t Street Beswick to Blackley to take me home because I wouldn't stop with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You say your parents had a lot of friends and they always came to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did they both share the same friends or did father have different friends to mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, they shared the same, it was always Mr and Mrs that came, there was no odd ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did they call in casually without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, yes, we didn't think it was necessary for to be asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Many people divide society i
nto different social classes or groups before 1918, did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another and can you tell me what they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh we used to think - we used to think it was awful for people that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 
worked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  in mills. Yes, we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Because me mother used to say, I wouldn't let a child of mine go in the mills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 This would be with your father being a clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember any other social differences - who were the most important people in your district do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - well a friend of mother and father's was a Mr Stanley, he lived on - I think it was somewhere up Crumpsall and he was the man that collected the bank at school. Bank at school, you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You thought he was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, we thought he was marvellous because he could go for all the pennies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Anyone else do you remember as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Now when all's said and done the shopkeepers you would come in contact with were as the dukes and duchess
es, used to think it was wonderful to be a princess or anything and at our school we used to have a - a play every Christmas, just after the Christmas and of course it was wonderful to be in those plays because you could stay up late, you were never in th
e street until you'd been in those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 plays}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 , your mother'd come and see to you that you weren't out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you thought shopkeepers were important too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I never went shopping. I never - no, I never went shopping because me older ones used to do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You never went out at all shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, no, they didn't trust me to go shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember who the shopkeepers mixed with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, I can't just remember. Well - we knew the Fays that had the grocers shop - sh
ops in the - who else was there now, and the Lees, they started very small you know, and we had - mother had a friend, a Mrs Renshaw and I used to go - when I got older I used to go to her shop and she taught me how to weigh things and everything and I us
ed to be able to mind it then on a Sunday afternoon if she wanted her husband had died and if she wanted to go to the cemetery her knew I could mind it for her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So that shop was open Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Oh those days the little shops made their money on a Sunday the same as they're doing today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Through staying open?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes, yes, because if you had visitors come unexpected you could always run out to the little shop and get something. That's what they miss in these communities now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who do you think the church people mixed with, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 priests}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  or the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well - oh no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why did you think it wonderful to see these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Because they had all these toffees in the shop and there's the pork and everything in the shops and we 
used to think it was wonderful to go look in shops because we never saw them lit up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who do you think the priests mixed with though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh we used to think - Father Hayes, he was a lovely priest and Father Evershed and they used to mix with the Fay
s and the Farleys and - the Pules and the different ones, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who do you think teachers mixed with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 The priest used - the priest used to come an his feast day and we used to always - there used to be a little collection for his pr
iest - his days. Well the teachers used to seem to mix sort of amongst one another and amongst the shopkeepers. Yes. And - we used to go to the - we used to take our dinners in a basket because there was four of us big ones going to Mount Carmel school, i
t was half a - half a - hours walk and we used to take our dinners in a basket and a brew of tea and go to the Farmyard Hotel opposite and they'd give us hot water. There was nothing at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You used to take your dinner with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You didn't have dinners at school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh nothing like that, no, there was nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember any employers and who they mixed with when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well you didn't - well I know me father used to be very friendly wi
th the Conolly's where - I used to hear him say about Chris Conolly and Joe Conolly and all of those you know, well they were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505  belonging }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 to the firm but it was limited company of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you think they mixed with other people too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Yes, and the
 O'Reilly's - yes because the - the O - the Connolly's and the O'Reilly's were mixed in marriage you see so of course that's how they - I used to entertain Martha O'Reilly and the different ones but you know we were all sent to bed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What sort of people do you think went to church and which went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well we thought, of course, like most people, we thought that we were right and - anyone that went to our church we thought, well, they were serious like we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What about the people who went to chapel - and the Protestant church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - yes, well we mixed with them. We had to mix with them as we grew older but - we didn't sort of - there were just that difference that you cling your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you think there was any social difference between the church people and the chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh now, in some cases there were some very nice people and my sister sang at the Wesleyan chapel for them, my sister at - at eight I think she was, she sang Flight of Ages and different things for
 to entertain at this - at church and I - we've always been taught to do - be right by people and I've helped at other churches }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  other schools since I've grown up but at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 same time there was just that that we thought we were right naturally. And we w
ere sorry for anyone that wasn't in our class. You know how I mean. Do you understand what I mean? We thought we were right and we thought we could perhaps help them, if we were being good, we could help them to come and see to our way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where you live
d were all the people in the working or lower class, do you think they all had the same standard of living or would you say they had different standards of living and can you describe the different standards of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I can't say that I - I cou
ld describe much of the standards of living because - well they all seemed to be very - we were all comfortable somehow. There was no one very poor.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You don't remember poor people in your district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. We lived on Moston Lane and it was - oppos
ite the Simpson Memorial and we used to have some very nice times going in there because there was four daughters, this Mr Kirkpatrick that was the caretaker had these daughters and each child was allowed to take a friend in if it was a very wet day we co
uld go in there, or they - an odd one could come to us but at that same time we didn't sort of - the parents didn't go in one another's houses, only just if it was something that they needed to ask about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you think of some families as being rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. Yes, of course. There was one or two down the side streets off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 
Moston}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  Lane, but - there boys and their inclined to be a bit rough, that's all. But we'd no trouble, I don't think you'll find anything wrong with Moston
 Lane, top of Moston Lane, for all the years that we lived about there, for - I never remember anyone saying that anything had gone on but of course we never saw a thing.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But do you remember some families as being rough as a whole, not just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, I was the rough one if there was any rough one because I used to go with me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 brothers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you think of them as - oh that's a rough family and that's a respectable family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well there might have been some down at - I'll tell you wher
e the rough people used to live and some of the children used to come to our school. They used to live down Factory Lane, off Moston Lane, now that was the rough quarter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why did you think it was rough, how did you think of it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well b
ecause - well because it - the curtains weren't nice and - you know - how I mean, used to think to yourself - and then they used to say, oh it's awful where they live, you know, so you sort of took it for granted that it was awful, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go down there and see whether it was awful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no, because we - we had to go home from school or else if we didn't go from school we got cuffed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you never actually went in a house that was regarded as rough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 There was only one time, a little girl - a girl died that was in our class and I went to see her and - I was frightened to death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I saw her lay there. And I never remember going again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes. There was a definite - definite distinction between a - a craftsman and a labourer. We'd say, oh he's only a labourer and at that time, the labourer - even when my father was at the carriage shop - the - we used to call the L.N.Y. carriage shop 
- the men only got sixteen and ten a week - for wages. But their families weren't rough, but their mothers'd - I suppose wash and that sort of thing to make it that - yes, yes. Oh no, there'd be an odd one perhaps in one of the streets off the - off like 
Barn Road there would - because it's a big road - there'd be an odd one but - I don't think I remember anyone getting in any serious trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who do you remember thinking of as respectable and why did you consider them respectable, what were the thing 
that made you feel they were respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh - they were very - you know, anyone that was very proper, like we had some friends, four sisters, the Morris's they were very sort of ah-la, one of them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  a councilor, I don't know if he's still living. Yes, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 a councilor, he was councilor Farrington and - they were very - you know, sort - we were supposed to be a little bit, you know, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well mother didn't mix much but she could always hold - you know, sort of be welcome and everyone liked her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did she think of everybody as the same though and did she regard some people as different to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well my mother never - never passed a
 remark about anyone because she had to be sort of very careful of what me father, but she was wonderful and she was as patient as job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What do you mean be careful about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well, if father liked anyone mother had to like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 She didn't have any option?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 The strict Victorian father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you think she saw herself as belonging to a special group a social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, my mother liked to think that we were someone a little bit different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Was it because of your father's job do you think?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well, she'd been - she'd been a pupil teacher herself and her sister was the headmistress of St George's, Ramsbottom and they were - but you see, my mother was born when her mother was forty-five and of cour
se naturally the others were grown up when she was born and it seems like history repeating itself because her brother left home when she was born, when my sister was born because it was late on. He thought that my father should have had more sense than w
ant any more family, yes, yes. And me mother had enough to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you think in those days as a child it was possible to move from one class to another, to move up in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How do you think they did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - I don't know, I suppose by being - smart and smartly dressed and that sort of thing, the dress made such a lot of difference.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You think dress made a lot of difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Definitely - appearance made a lot of difference, yes. And if you were sort of we weren't allowed to use slang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You weren't allowed to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, oh dear no, I never heard my father swear. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember anybody who did move up in the world and how do you think they did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - no, well - there's the - the girls i
n the class. And then a friend of my father's got to be the Mayor of Manchester and he was the Mayor for three years, three times, Sir Daniel McCabe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did they manage it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well of course it was - he was a bachelor and it was by his own
 efforts and by going about and my father used to be in same trade and there was - sort of - they were very popular. Now was the Lord Mayor for three years, three times so he must have been a very popular man. Now he wasn't - he wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  and he - he - his sister worked for him, they had a works in town called McCabe and it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  millinery and that sort of thing. Now - he used to be very friendly with father so - with father so of course, he was one of the upper ten.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Do you remember anybody going down in the world and what do you think caused it?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 With this man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You feel that drink caused it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, yes, he used to say what a pity. Now my father was very friendly with Leslie Stewart that wrote all those songs, yes, yes, well 
Leslie Stewart was a friend of me father's and he moved in the same - circle an Dan McCabe and they were heart - broken about their daughter Amy you know because the song was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Mammy}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  may, when you; grow up some day. Well now that girl }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  a - a young man
 and they went to London and - after they'd been to London some time all of a sudden she was missing and the father didn't hear from her and he tried all ways to get in touch with her. However, about four years ago it was in the paper that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember anyone being called a real lady or a real gentleman when you were a child and why do you think they were called this?

