\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh I never saw the landlord, no, but I think it were about six and eightpence a week I remember me mother saying, you know, put this away and put that right and leave it for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember how your mother felt about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh - no - she was all right. My mother was a very mild type of person. She was ladylike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You don't remember your parents ever having to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 
Well they did because when it came to me I was the fourth and they had to sort of start struggling then to make ends meet but - they never had to get in debt.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And they never had to go for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. No. My mother managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But she had a hard time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes she did have a hard struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8659632\charrsid15489505 Well really - well really I think we used to play some Jones's and Root\rquote s and different people who were sort of - in 
business, you know, now you asked me about business and I couldn't think before, Grocott's they had joinery business and then - the Jones's, they used to live in the dip just by the - by the clough and we used to go there a lot, they had a nice house and 
you know, we sort - of used to go there and - well - I think that we used to mix with the other class.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What class would you say this was?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Not swearing and - you know, not sort of being rough about anything, not - not quarrelling. I think we did 
'cos we - we were each sort of told it was no use being poor and seeming poor. Now, my sisters, the two of them always dressed - were dressed alike when were young and so years afterwards I said to my mother, you know ma, I don't think I was treated fair 
because I always had to have what they'd finished with. So she said, yes, well you had two t- their one. Yes. Yes.
