\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Could you talk to your dad or share your worries with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did your parents expect you to behave toward them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well - we - we used to always to have to be sort of - afra
id, you know what I mean, we were afraid to say anything wrong, afraid that we should want - if we wanted to go anywhere you had to muster all your courage up to ask could you go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did they expect you to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh well, we all loved one another, we all used to - used to laugh about them, what they used to sort of - on the sly, we used to say, oh walk in front of papa and, you know, that sort of thing. Just have a little bit of fun between ourselves but we did
n't dare let him think we laughed at him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Suppose a child outside hit you were you told to hit back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You were told to hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6294164\charrsid15489505 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up - to be and what did they consider important in life?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
That you should get on and stand on your own two feet. And being one of six they would know it, you would have to learn to look after yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6294164\charrsid15489505 Do you know what they thought was important in life?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well they thought that we should get on and we should go and be right with one another, love one another and my mother would have - you must never go to them without - if you've been cross you must never go to bed without you say goodnight to one anoth
er and never go out of the house before you would say - without saying good morning. Because }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 don't know what'll happen during the day. And you don't know what'll happen in the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Suppose grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. Children had to be seen and not heard and run away and do something else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Suppose you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen, who punished you and what were you punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Bed. Bed for a start, you go upstairs to bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who punished you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Me father was the one, me ma would say - I'll tell your father now. Which was a mistake, they should hit you when you've done a thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you ever smacked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I was, I've had a good - a few good hidings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who from, your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well me - me father most, you know, me ma'd tell me pa I'd done something and he just sort of give you a - bat and up the stairs you go,}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505  no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  tea for you, no tea for you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember a particular}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505  occasion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
I'll tell you - I was punished and I felt very hurt about this. I was told to come straight home from school and I was coming home with a girl and we went in a shop and my fat
her was on the cars and he passed us going in this shop and me ma said, I want - I told you to come home, where have you been? I said, well I came home with such a body but I've come straight home. My father, you're telling lies, I saw you go in a shop, w
hat did you go in the shop for? Oh it was - it didn't dawn on me that I'd told a lie, you know, I said, oh I went with - I think it was a girl called Charlotte Bremner, I said, I went with her and - she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 going for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  a message, but it was a sweet shop you s
ee and he thought I'd been in a sweet shop and I had no money for sweets. So - I got told off for telling lies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I felt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you resent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I did, and I've resented it for years. You know how I men. I t
hought, if; ever I have a child I'll take notice of what it says rather than punish it for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You resented the fact that you thought you'd been punished for nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Would you say you received the ideas about how to beh
ave from both your parents or do you think one played a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Ma played more important than pa. Yes, because - she told us to be polite, we were supposed to be polite and always to - you know, always sort of stand by for
 anyone older than yourself and always be kind to children and don't hurt an animal, if you don't like an animal don't hurt it and it - don't be afraid of a dog because if you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 let it}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  see you're afraid it jumps at you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your mother was a kindly person then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, you always got a cake, extra little cake on your birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh - very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have a party or have guests in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh no. No parties until you grew up. Sometimes you - you got a book - a little book, story book as you got older but you got an extra sweet or something, that's all you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You never had a party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no. The first party I ever remember was when my eldest sister was twenty-one and then we had a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What about Christmas Day, did you do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - only our own family and then we played snap or something after for the evening. No, we didn't go anywhere Chris
tmas. Only to grandma Joyce's - we used to go to grandma's, I think I told you went and we took a side of a tram up in - we'd to walk such a long way from the - the tram office - the - it used to be a stables where Arthur A Batts are now and that used to 
be the stables and we'd to walk right down into Blackley village and we were only young but anyway, we'd had this punch, we thought it was punch we'd have and we were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You didn't get a Christmas present either you said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, we alway
s got something in our stockings. We got an apple, an orange and perhaps a few sweets and I think I got a little - I got a doll one time, one - a wooden doll with - it's hair - hair painted and it's painted down here and it's - you know, just sort of wood
en arms and legs and a frock on it and I thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we had - yes, our Eddie played the violin and - ma used to be able to play the piano. Yes, ma used to play the piano and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you make music as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. Ma used to play for the hymns and the different things for us. And pa was a singer and on Thursday night a Mr Jack Nuttall, a friend of his, used to sing - used to sing duets at the concerts and he used to co
me and practice. And then he was teaching some girls - choir at one time and we used to - we were let up one night we stayed up and we were peeping through the - the - the nick of the door and we saw them all in front of the mirror and we just went in and
 laughed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Looking at themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your - parents play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh sometime - ma'd play snap with us and - we'd play - try and play whist. They taught us to play cards, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have a lot of papers or magazines or books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
We were - on at night time we used to sit and have question and answers. Yes, me ma used to ask us what was this and what was that. And what have you done at school, used to always have to be telling what we'd done
 at school and we used to answer the catechism, we used to have to sort of learn that first and then she'd say what - what - you know, what subjects have you been using? Well - geography was my favourite and essays, writing compositions, you know, from be
ing very young, but I were never much good as a painter. Sorry I couldn't do any painting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have papers in the house or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  papers but - we were never allowed to see the paper. No, were never allowed to see an evening paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I don't know, but me father used to just get the paper and I think he used to get the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Dispatch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  in the morning and he'd come home at lunch time, if we were on holiday or anything we'd see him, he'd c
ome home for his lunch and he'd always have a glass of beer after his dinner. You know what I mean, he sort of was just so - well collared up and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What does this mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 White collar, always white collar and cuffs and white hand
kerchiefs, and of course the same thing applied to me brothers when they went to work, we had to make sure that they always had good - fresh clean handkerchief every day and a nice collar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No - we got prizes at s
chool, I got David Copperfield and Danesbury House and - oh different religious publications I got. And we used to swap them with one - I wouldn't dare say swap then but I said it now, we used to change them with one another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 As a child do you ever remember a funeral in the family and who attended and what kind of clothes they wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes. Well now my grandma was buried and they brought, we went down to Carruthers Street for - to see there - to see - start the funeral off from there and they to
ok us to Moston and when we got to the Ben Brierly me mother said we are not going on to Carruthers Street, we're - staying - we're going home. So we went home. So we never went to any party, we never heard of - you know what I mean, we didn't go to the t
ea. They would have a tea but we didn't go. It was for grown ups, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember who attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. I went and - my brother and me two sisters and me mother and father. There was like - was it six of us went and there was a coach for us be
cause we were the eldest son's children but when we got to Ben Brierly coming home me mother said, we're not going to - the house, we're not going down there because, she said, it's the trouble of bringing the children home again and we're not going.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So there was a funeral and a tea afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. We didn't go for the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember what kind of clothes they wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - I think you had just - I just had a black frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It had to be black did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I had to have a 
black frock and I got some new shoes and they hurt me and I was crying for the shoe - 'cos the shoes hurt me and me aunt said to me - me Auntie Nellie said to me mother, you know, Mary must have loved her grandma, she has cried. It was me feet that was cr
ippling me. Well they put them in the front of the hearse - in front of the carriage. Vera was two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. And - they put them in the front of the coach - the - like under the driver's seat just behind the driver's seat, it was a litt
le place like a little compartment and that's where they put them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So they didn't have a hearse at all for the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, not for a child, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you remember this funeral do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I remember it was at Moston in a proper ground, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And did you have a tea after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It was just a quiet funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, 'cos she was only a baby, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours friends or relations and who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh me mother. Yes. Yes, me mo
ther always - our Eddie took me out one Sunday to some friends of his and - I couldn't believe it, they were all giving me money, I wondered - I didn't realize, I thought, you know, money, I thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you wanted to go visiting again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well they were going to Australia as a matter of fact, it was some people named Dare and they lived just behind Mount Carmel school and it was Jimmy Dar his pal was and he said, oh bring your little sister. So of course they took me and - oh they w
ere making such a fuss and giving me this - I couldn't eat me dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we used to go to Philip Wymans on Oldham Road and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Me mother. And then one time I went out with a teacher shopping
, she had a pet dog and she wanted to get some meal for it, some special stuff and we walked along of Oldham Road 'cos I said I'd seen it in the shop window. Anyway we went - I used to go shopping with a teacher. I was very fond of our teacher, she was ca
lled Miss Nightingale and she was - oh she was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no. Oh only once. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 
We were walking in a procession and me father was bringing me home and - it would just happen, I'd a hat and veil on and the veil caught on a railing, of course I tore it so - me father was very happy.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 For I tore the veil - he wasn't happy I mean. He was very annoyed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And this was the only time you ever remember going out with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Never took me any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go out on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh now we all went on a Bank Holiday to Bugget Hill Clough. And we never used to - they used to have tables outside on the way to the band stand and ma used to bake and we'd go there and take the tea
 and - my brother had been paddling in the little brook and so of course when we saw the path we were feeling a bit bothered. I might tell you we'd done it at dinner time. However he told me father about me brother paddling you see, and he shouldn't have 
d
one anyway of course our day was spoiled. But we used to buy - we used to get hot water there, they'd have the teapots and you'd get the hot water and you'd have - sit at this table and have your tea and stay in the club - clough all afternoon, it was won
d
erful to go with your father. Well then - on August Bank Holiday as we got older, used to take us to Belle Vue. Oh, it was wonderful to go to Belle Vue. Yes. We had brown tea cakes and - you know, white currant tea cakes and all sorts of things. We though
t it was just wonderful, you didn't - and you used have those with all those hundreds and thousands on the top, you could get a cake for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 tuppence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 . Yes, that was hundreds and thousands, yes, well, used to have one of those after your tea 'cos you'd buy those where you got your hot water so as you could get your hot water. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go away for a holiday and how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well now - now I didn't go away for a holiday but me father took the boys. Me father and mother and Vera went and we - 
we were home then and we looked after them, that was - just before the end of the summer before she died. Well then - we - we girls didn't get a holiday. But me father took the boys, me father took the boys but he didn't take us and they could have a priv
ilege ticket, you see. They could go for very little to Blackpool, they could go free practically but not the girls. He didn't bother about taking us - girls out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, because - well I suppose he - he thought we were a bit of a nuisance.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 He thought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  were a nuisance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you never had a holiday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Not with me father, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you spend your Saturdays as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well, we used to play about, used to just play about or have a walk to the clough or 
- me sister used to - me eldest sister used to take us up the road towards Heaton Pork for a walk, we used to - and think it was lovely to get some of those flowers that we know now that they're only weeds like perfly flowers you know. Yes. Yes, and she u
s
ed to take us over the road and if you were getting tired and we got to these - these little cottages sometimes she'd say, now, you'll have to run, now be careful and be very - we'd be tired - and we'd perhaps start grumbling about coming home and she'd s
ay, now you'll have to be - quiet passing here because there's a gipsy lives in there and if she sees you and you're naughty you know she'll just cut your head off and put your blood in that. That did us. We'd run like mad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You were afraid of gypsies were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What did you do on Sundays, did you wear special Sunday clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - yes, and you went to church and as soon as you came home from church you took them off. Yes. And if you were going to Sunday school in the aftern
oon perhaps you would be - have an apron - have a pinafore on and manage like that until half past five and then when you'd come home and you have your tea, you would take your things off and put an old - put your other frock on while you're sitting about
 the house playing cards or whatever you're doing, ludo, or whatever you're playing, you still had that old frock on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your parents didn't think it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, they didn't. No, no, they thought you should play, they said it would quicken your brain to be counting numbers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Would they let you play out in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no, not in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did they think that playing games in the street and working, did they think working was wrong on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes, they used to do those days, they - nobody worked on Sunday. But - they used to think that any of those games reckoning up the numbers, it sort of gave you that interest in numbers and it quickened your 
brain a bit. Then my - one time my sister went to work for a - a pawnbroker on Rochdale Road so every Sunday and we used to write the - the - she used to bring books of tickets home and we used to write - Anne of Sand Street, there used to be a Sand Stree
t you see on Rochdale Road, Anne of Sand Street and we all had to learn and we all did those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You helped with the tickets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, so as to learn to write properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did she like working in a pawnshop, did she find it interesting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - well - I - I think it was beneath her, between you and I, she worked in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Afflex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  in the counting house and it was - she liked the extra money but she didn't like the type of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 She would see life there thought wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh definitely - the wrong sort though. The wrong sort of life to suit us, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Regular did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well they did for a long time and then it got too much, you know, they didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You went to Sunday school you told me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we used to go to Sunday school at Mount Carmel, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well no, there weren't. There weren't. And me mother never encouraged you to go on anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, because she said you hear of such funny things happening. Me mother wanted to keep her chicks somewhere around about, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you in any other social clubs or anything belonging to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Ooh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. I was in the choir and I was also picked always for in the concerts. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you were in concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Just Christmas concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we used to - they used to do play, they used to do Sleeping Beauty and Punch and Judy and - oh wha
t else was it - no, they used to - have a different concert each year and it would always be in January and somewhere round about the fifteenth or the twenty-second you know, on a Monday night and Tuesday night and we used to have to go but of course they
 
always came to meet you to bring you home because every entry - if I passed an entry at night I would have been terrified. When we went out you see and you - you nervous of going out. I was Fairy Rose, could you imagine me, Fairy Rose? And then I was a Ja
panese in something else. In the Willow Pattern we did the Willow }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Pattern and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 I was a Japanese and - oh used to have some - cretonne like and just like kimono and some - two flowers in your hair you know and you\rquote re a Jap - you're a Jap - you're a Japanese we think. That was it. She used to make the things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your mother used to make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. Oh yes, she had to do because we'd no way of spending and getting them you know. No, no, me mother was a very careful - and her a wonderful housewife and a wonderful mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You thought the world of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes. You're afraid of your father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You were afraid of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes I was, yes. Yes, only some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Just because he was strict do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, he had - perhaps he had t
he best - he evidently had the best intentions and he came to me when he was ill - when he came to me the last time he - he was ill and he said, our Ellen, I've come to you to be nursed and I want you to do the same for me as you did for your mother. And 
I - I buried - saw to all the burying for me mother and everything, the others were all miles away, but they all came round when they wanted what was left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You felt a lot for your mother though?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I have because - well she could understand me so m
uch different than the others. And she used to say when she saw me working at Broad Street shop - I never thought a child of mine'd work this hard because she thought it was awful to have to work you know and - meet the different people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But of course if you were left a widow this would happen wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes, but it was the different class of people I'd come into you see because they'd come in from the Horse Shoe on a Saturday night you see, she - she came - I let Christine go to her auntie's f
or the weekend so she says, oh well, they'd come down and they came down and - she saw - he came and he'd had drink and they were having their suppers, you know, and it wasn't very nice and it wasn't really nice little bit to have to do so she was very up
set about that 'cos she thought it was terrible. But as far as my mother was concerned I never heard her swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was she very religious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - she was good but she wasn't too religious, you know what I mean, she was very genuine. And she'd help a
nybody. She'd help anybody, yes, she was very helpful. And I think that - I'd do anything for anyone round here. Mr Bouncell'll tell you. He said, I've been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did the church run a temperance club when you were a child? And were you a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, we never had anything. No. To say - when you were old you'd sign the pledge but I never remember signing any pledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You don't remember a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. No. Suppose to live at - on Moston Lane and she'd been called Nancy Dickybird. She wa
s - now she was a - a character in - in Manchester at that - when I was very young, it must have been in the - 1890's and then she used to - eventually - she was a terrible drinker and then after a while she must have - been reformed and she used to go an
d
 stand on Moston Lane and say to people outside the pub, how she'd been saved. How she was called Nancy Dickybord, she was a familiar person in a Manchester history because she'd been a drinker and then gone - yes. And wanted everyone else to do about - d
o without drinking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh absolutely, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Me father said it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What about prayers, were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we used to say them - when we were very little and it -
 when we were young and it was cold we used to kneel downstairs and say them so that we'd only must have to go upstairs and hop into bed. Well, otherwise you'd - you were trusted to say your prayers upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 And you always did, did you?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well, yes, and sometimes you'd say, God forgive me, I'm tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever say prayers as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. When - you know, sort of when there was anything sort of - worrying me mother we used to all say our prayers together downstairs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your mother liked you to pray together if you were worrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, me mother used to sort of - rely on us and she used to say you know, Almighty God always hears the prayers of a child. And we used to think that because she said that that whateve
r we asked for it would be all right you know but it wasn't always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you feel disappointed when it wasn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. 'cos he was a Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did he ever talk about his views and why he held them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
No, he used to say to us, we used to say, who are you voting for pa, because when it was calling he was red you know, and he used to say, now that is one's own business and - and all your life you must remember, never 
tell anyone who you're voting for. But as years went on we knew he was a rank Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You don't know why he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, only just that he was a rank Conservative and he must have had a reason - his own reason for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your mother take any interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Me mother had no interest in politics at all. She'd enough to do in the house without politics. Voted Conservative because our doctor was a Conservative and he'd been very good to us. Always came to us if we needed him you know. 'Course he got paid.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember your mother and father voting before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 
Well - yes, they - I think they always voted Conservative because - in Blackley Doctor Couch was the Conservative candidate and Lord Crawley was the Liberal.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 They never helped at the election, did they take any part in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no, not - not to - you couldn't afford to if you were - if you were in business. You couldn't afford to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you feel your father was ever under this type of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I think that he imagined that he would be. Yes, because you see, they thought that they w
ere employing you and you should sort of go and I always remember hearing my father say you were given your brains to think for yourself and I'm thinking for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So even though he felt under pressure he still voted his way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 He pleased himself. He pleased himself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But he did feel that he was under pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes, to a certain extent I think that everyone - the majority of people thought to a certain extent they were because you see, was always those people who used to say, neve
r argue about politics or religion because - if you well, the man who works next to you. If he's opposite in his views he'll try and force his views on you. To say, and especially when the Labour came up they said, why are they bothering - going causing a
l
l this trouble because the country has to pay for them whereas the Conservatives, they've something to conserve, their conserving all the money and that in the country whereas the Labour people are just letting it go. Well that's my understanding of me fa
ther's ideas about - Conservatism, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their spare time in your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - they didn't have very much time off work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your father worked long hours didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Th
ey didn't have much time off work because - if they had a holiday - they were sort of - he would take us out one day and go out on his own another day, go bowling or something, I don't know but - we always were allowed one day out with him round about Aug
ust Bank Holiday and it - and Easter Monday and he'd always took us to his people at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So your dad played bowls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did he go to races or bet or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh now and again he'd like to go to the races. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And he liked to bet did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Always on a Whit Friday he used to go to the races, Manchester race course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, she didn't have time. Oh no, no, say many a time, poor ma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did she never go out to enjoy herself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, but - as we got older we used to see that she went out to the pictures and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You used to take her did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. She loved Shirley Temple. And Charl - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Charlie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  Chaplin, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But she didn't when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When your father got home from work in the evenings do you remember how many evenings a week he'd stay in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I don't think me father stayed in much but we were in bed most of the time, you know, when we we
re very young, but when he used to sing and he used to go to the Land League, that was a club on Rochdale Road where he'd meet Dan McCabe and the different ones. Then he'd go to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Patrick
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  - he used to be a - a man for the different clubs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 He was a sociable man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did he go to pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh I suppose he did. But my - my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your mother go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. No, she wouldn't go with him. And my youngest brother said to the lady opposite that - not very far
 away from us a lady used to come and see mother sometimes and they had a pub and he said to her, you know, my mother wishes all the public houses would burnt up, but not yours Mrs Wilson 'cos I love you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, nothing to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What about funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes, of course, they had to pay insurances, you - they belonged to the Royal liver because my Uncle was a super in the Royal Liver at Oldham ; so they belonged to the Royal Liver.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh all right, they'd help you if they felt like it but if they didn't feel like it they'd tell you to get it done yourself, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was there anyone you felt particularly close to as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 My brother that was next to me, he was my world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes, he was because he thought that - a lot about me and I thought about him and I didn't see him for thirty-seven years but I went to America to see him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you absolutely worshipped him did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 As a child who did you play with, your brothers and sisters or neighbours children?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Brothers - brothers. Yes. Played piggy with 'em, played whatever they were playing and one day me father came out and was disguste
d with me for climbing over the - railings. He said, there's an old pair of trousers upstairs, go and get them on. I'm ashamed of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What kind of games did you play, do you remember what your childhood games were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - I used to play ropes and - piggy and rounders and we had - there was a young man, I don't know if ever you remember the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Hippodrome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 on the stage, the three men, Lovejoy and Enoch and - well he used to - we used to have Enoch - Enoch used to come and play with us and we used to go trying to learn tap dancing down the bend at Moston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You mean the Enoch who was later in this used to play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes, and we used to go to the pictures with him because we used to have a penny and a pass from one of the shops, you kno
w, when we got to about fifteen, we used to go on the back row at the pictures. The back row, they were just forms, and you'd all go like this, brothers and sisters all together you know, we'd all go one night a week. A penny - a penny a ticket - a penny 
and a ticket, that was your outing for a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where did you play as a child, in the yard or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 garden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  or street or in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - well there's a field near us and we used to play in the field mostly. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well if you got dirty of course you're in and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents allow you to play with anyone or were there certain children they said, now don't play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes, they didn't say well, they used to sa
y, now don't play with him because; he's a naughty boy, or something because I heard him talking to some - I heard him swearing and you don't go with them you know. But you'd no need to because I had three brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You always played together as a family did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. And then there was a girl, lived a bit out - two girls lived }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 
further}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  up and we - they used to come and play with us and me brother - me eldest brother used to go out with one now and again you know, they used to go for a little bit 
of a walk but we used to go swimming this - these other girls and myself, we joined the Osmond Street baths and we used to go swimming and that, good lot of our time we spent at the baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you belong to any youth organisations,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have any hobbies while you were at school, have pets or collect anything or do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. We used to have to sew. Yes, used to have to sew. Learn all kinds of sewing. Me mother used sit with me mother and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 She used to teach you to sew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. She would let -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 She wanted you to be good housewives did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 She was, yes, and she never - I don't think my mother ever spent a penny wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You are fond of your mother aren't you, from all you've told me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You said you'd like to be like your mother didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well, I - I'd - yes, I - I hope my children have the same memory of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you go fishing or for walks or bicycling at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did I -? Used to go fishing - 'til I fell in. And got a good hiding when I came home for falling in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You went with your brothers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you come to fall in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - me sister was with us and she said, now - now if you can just - and there was some nice flowers and I thoug
ht I'd like some of those flowers so she said, if you'll just jump over that, you know, you'll just get it. Now jump. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 And instead of jumping I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15489505  
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 jumped }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 in so of course I was all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 mucky}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505  so she took me frock off and tried to dry it on the railings and everything, anyway I got caught just the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15489505  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 same for dirtying this nice frock and I - had shoes with white buttonholes and they all were slutched up you know, I - well I got in trouble when I got - sent to bed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who did this - your mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Better get up to bed before your father sees you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you take part in any sports as a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I used to like climbing. Used to like climbing with them and - going walks, I used to go walks with a girl called Olive }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 Murphy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 , we used to go round Moston on a Sunday mornin
g when we'd been to church and we hadn't to get dirty. Remember having banana bonnets and everything and going all round Moston, where - where its all built up now, Notash Road there used to be a little shop and it was called Granny Copses and we were ver
y thirty and we both had ha'penny so we'd go and get ha'porth of pop - ha' 'porth of mineral on a Sunday morning. But Dolly Murphy they had a shop and she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505  had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  an uncle that was always giving her coppers and he'd give me one you see, go on off out you two, here, go and get yourself something. So of course we'd go and get ha'porth of herb beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You never took part in any sport thought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever go to theatres, concerts or music halls or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Not - not as we were older - oh no, not while we're at school. Oh no, you couldn't go to the cinema when you were at school, the only concerts you went to was the one you were in. No, we weren't allowed out at night when we were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Not until you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. No, not 'til you went to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents give you any pocket money, how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 We got threepence. When you were fourteen you got threepence. Thirteen. Before you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How much would you get before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 We'd get 
about tuppence I think and then when you were fourteen you got a penny in the shilling if you - work. Yes. And that had to buy your hair ribbons. If you were - because you didn't have - your mother could give you a piece that she'd made with a gimped edge
 you know and fasten you up but otherwise you'd to buy your own and you got three - penny in a shilling for your spends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You got nothing as a child you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh and when we were very young, no, we only had sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you tell me your dad bought the sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Yes, Mother Nobletts - we never knew what it was go in a shop and buy them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It used to be called Mother Nobletts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your dad bought the sweets and then divide them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. Me dad - me father bought the sweets and they were 
put in a cupboard and you got so many on the Saturday, that was your Saturday and then as the weeks went - as the week went on you'd perhaps do something and you wouldn't you know, they'd say, now such a thing and you be a very - you know, be a good girl 
and do that, something and you'd get a toffee for doing it you see. And that's how the toffees worked out all the week. I don't know how much he must have spent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you had to be good or you didn't get any sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no. If you did anything wrong
 you got nothing. I'll tell you what we used to get, we used to have - cod liver oil and malt all winter. We used to have to go - every - every night, we used to have - me ma used to say, now come on, just before you go to bed. And you'd each take your sp
oon and go to the side of the cupboard and she kept it on the top shelf and she used to stand on the step or on a chair and she would hand each of you a spoonful of cod liver oil and malt and that's what kept us all right I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What other kinds of medicine did you have, anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Senna. Always senna. It was senna pods put in the teapot of a Friday. Friday night. Senna pods, you used to put it in the teapot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 In with the tea was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. So a as - me ma - yes, me ma used to do th
at so as we didn't notice it was senna. You wouldn't notice, she'd say, she - if you said, oh this tea - it's a bit funny ma. She said, it's a new kind of tea and it's all right, you know, and then in later years she told us what she'd done. Every Friday 
night so that we would be all right and we wouldn't be wanting to go to the toilet too much at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Every Friday was senna pods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes, it's true. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I went at - at - I think I went at four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you go morning or afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
I went to - at - when I was four we went to St Peters, Blackley because it was a - a non-Catholic school, it was a Church of England, but we couldn't walk all the way to ours because it was 
half an hours walk. So we went to St Peters church and we didn't have to pay school money there but when we went to Mount Carmel we had to pay school money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 St Peters church was a baby school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. We went to the infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you go morning and afternoon, what time did you start and what time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
I can't remember but I know that our teacher was called Miss Crossley and for years we had - I - I thought she was - ooh, she'd the loveliest red hair and I always laugh abo
ut - think about her and just before I came here I destroyed the picture of us in the class - the photograph that they took, and she's there with her square thing you know and - and sort of - but she was lovely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. I did. And I wanted to be a teacher, they wanted me to be a teacher but me father wouldn't let me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 St Peters you went to, was it boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What kind of school was it, was it church or council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - Mount Carmel? Oh St Peters was - yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 St Peters was just an ordinary school, a junior school I suppose we'd call it today but you were on a gallery. Yes, like you're - you're a bit raised up on a gallery like. There was the rows - the rows of forms there and - the - I remem
ber they used to give us the pen and some paint and a paper and you'd to make things on the paper, like as though it would be - well really anyone does it that's making a leaf I think, you know, they would put a little dab on, well that's what we had to d
o.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember if you went afternoons as well as a child to St Peters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
I think I must have done, I think we had to go. I think we had to go, I'll not be sure, if you started to go to school you'd to go proper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It sounds like a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, it was down - off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Dominic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  Street, Blackley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who took you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Our Eddie. Our Eddie, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You say you liked school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh I did. I got a biscuit the first day for saying a cow has cloven hoof. That was a lot those days 'cos they didn't buy many }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 biscuits}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You say you liked your teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How old were you when you went to Mount Carmel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I must have been about six or seven when I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember the times you went in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh I had to go all day there. And - I went with the others and they took their dinner in a basket. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember the time in the morning you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, we'd to be there for nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What time did you finish for dinner,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
We didn't get home 'til half past four I think. We finished school between four and half past and we'd to walk home to Blackley then, back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It was a long way then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who took you when it was such a long way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Our Madge and Chris, 'cos they were big girls, yes. And me brother went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you had your dinner there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You used to take sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Used to take - yes, and - and we used to - our Madge used to go over to the Farm
 Yard Hotel and they'd give her hot water because they tram shed was next to and she used to say, you know, there's rats in there, so we never used to go in there, but she used to go over to the Farm Yard and they were - the waiter'd always give us the ho
t water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where did you eat your meals then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 In the school, in a little room - cloakroom in the school because there was no convenience at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No place at all for dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were there no nearer schools or was it because it was a Catholic school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It was a Catholic school. Yes. Yes, and when we were seven you were supposed to come to the use of reason and go to a Catholic school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was this boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes - no, the boys were in one school and we were in the other school, the girls had the new school, the boys had the old school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What did you think of this school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - at first I didn't like it but then I got used to it and I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why didn't you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well it was a big change from being a mixed school I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you like the teachers here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh yes, I loved me teachers. I did really, yes, I did. But Sister Mary Patty was very good, she was the headmistress, but the only thing wa
s she used to give us the cane if we were late. And never made any excuses. You never took any excuses for you being late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What else did she punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 For being late or if you'd broken anything or if you'd made any blots on anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And it was always the cane was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, she had a nice big cane and she used to whack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 On your hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, on your legs, the back of your legs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You didn't like her for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, you'd get one on your hand and one your leg as you were walking away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were they all nuns who taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, there were three nuns. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 
There was Sister Mary Patty, Sister Austina and - oh - oh another nun, I forget her name but they were a little bit on the - can I say - the hard side, because they didn't have the - temptations that other people'd do to love you, you know what I mean. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Can you understand what I mean, they couldn't see any reason for you doing something that you'd done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 If you did anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 They didn't have the understanding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, no, they couldn't understand you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you thought they were very strict did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember if the teachers emphasised certain things as important like manners or tidiness or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. You hadn't to be late and the ways - way that you spoke. You hadn't to cut any words short. You always had - you know, like today, and in many cases people sort of - cut their words off, don't they, and consequently us
ed to be pulled up for that. And used to be pulled up if your shoes weren't polished and if you'd a torn pinafore on or anything, you know, if you tore your pinafore, 'cos used to have pinafores those days and go to school with a pinafore on. But - otherw
ise I didn't much across with them because I was always very willing. If they asked me to wash the ornaments I'd go and wash them or - water the plants or do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do your remember anything else at school you were taught was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
We were taught to be honest. And when you got your reference from school they said, now you're going from school with a good reference and I hope that you'll always keep it that way. Always be honest. Never take }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 anyone\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  money, never take any money that you're not entitled to. And give a good days work for a days pay. That's what we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents take an interest in your school work, did they ever visit the school and the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. They did. And - the teacher wanted to k
now would they let me go in for teaching, Miss Nightingale wanted - she said, I'll help her and what was that that you used to get a book - she said, I'll get that for her and - now what was it called, Derwent something. I know there was some book that wo
uld help you on. And me father said, don't bother thank you, he said, because she'll be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 before she's twenty-one so it's no use wasting time with her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And your father didn't think you should go because of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you regret this much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - yes, I used to resent being sort of - not getting the chance but at the same time I made me life and it didn't have to matter.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you feel though that your father made a distinction between the girls and the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I'll tell you what - yes, he did. My father thought that the boys should have an attention but the girls'd grow up, get }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  and be housewives and that'd be the end of the girls. No career for girls he didn't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You still feel he did hold this distinction and you still resent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Oh yes. Well I think this way, it would have been such a different avenue in life, for me, if I could have done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 At this school did the children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well they had to be mixed. They were a mixed type of children for the simple reason, they were rich and poor. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You noticed this distinction as a child did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well of course, your one that could take the most money if it was anything 
- to be collected for was the one that - well, I'll say if there was any collections for the feasts of this one or that one, oh there's always some that'd bring more than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 others. And consequently, oh well, you know, as much as to say, you know this muc
h that people'd say, you can understand it now, they'd say, oh well, you know, Mrs Such a body, she'd be all right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Their children would bring more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you find that this made them treat children, some children different to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well yes, they used to say, oh never mind about them, they never bother, you know, they don't bother - I don't know whether they don't tell their parents or what. Not us, but they said it about a certain - one or two, they said, you don't
 know whether the child tells them or not because the child just comes and say, oh pleas miss, I forgot to ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And they treated them differently if they didn't bring much for the collection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you think this was fair or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It wasn't fair, definitely wasn't fair because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you feel it as a child or just now you're older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Now that I'm older and I look back I think to myself, well, they were a little bit hard with those that couldn't - if there was 
a big family that they couldn't have given more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But you didn't feel it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It didn't - no, well you don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were there any gangs in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh gangs, no, we hadn't to think about gangs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Were there any children left out of things, do you remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - there perhaps would be, the Factory Lane children were left out of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Because like if it was something to be bought for them to wear, a uniform or anything, they - didn't want to wear a 
uniform sort of style and I suppose perhaps if the truth was known the people couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So they got left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You finished at this school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I m
ust have been going up for fourteen but I left at the Christmas because we moved and - we moved and it was too far to go to school and I hadn't been well and so doctor said I - you know, like I could finish. They said at school, and I went to Lewis's.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 This was when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What year did you say you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 1894.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You've got a good memory haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, 1894.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Would you have stayed on longer at school if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I would have loved to have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you go to any part time evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I did, I used to go to Lily Lane school at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What did you do at evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I went for business correspondence and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes I did, many a time. Yes, I - I - many a time I used to think, well - I wish I would have been able to stay at school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Because you got a certain finish, didn't you, if you were allowed to go to school a bit longer there was a - a better finish to you, you thought. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Finish school life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you think you benefited from your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. Well I - I've never been so - I've always managed to get through.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Talking about your education generally as you look back what are your feelings about it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well I really think that - on the whole you - we can't grumble. But I think today I think they're getting too much education and they're not - they're getting the schooling and all these lovely 
universities are being built and there's so many drop outs that it makes you feel that they're wasting money because there's some that have been ambitious to get to a school and then when they've got there it - they - they've lost interest. But they have 
to go for the certain length of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But looking back at your childhood you felt your schooling was satisfactory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 To a certain extent I would like to have had a further education or else I wouldn't have gone to night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So that you could have gone on to teach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have a part time job while you were at school to earn spends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Oh no. No, I used to go to that friend of me mother's and go in the shop and - she didn't used to pay me anything but she'd buy me a - a l
ittle pinafore piece or something so that I could make it myself. A piece of gingham or - if I'd minded the shop perhaps on a Sunday afternoon she'd buy me - she'd say, now I've got a nice piece of gingham here and you can make yourself a frock or you can
 make yourself a blouse or, you know, sort of something like that, and - and - but I didn't have any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You never got money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember what your first job was when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Lewis's. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I applied for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Not through a Labour Exchange or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh, there was no Labour Exchange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you see it, - did you see it in the paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. Well - me ma must have seen it in t
he paper because they - she said - she said they were wanting girls at Lewis's and I - and I would have to go down. So I went down. Me sister was in catering and she wanted me to go to Parkers with her and I went down - and I never was very fond of washin
g
 up to tell the truth, and I went down - no, and I went down to Parkers supposing to go for me interview and when I got there and I saw all the tables - all the tables beautifully laid out with silver and that I thought, well they're not getting me here c
leaning silver and I never went for the interview, I went back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You went to Lewis's and you were a shop assistant in gloves and you did a little bit of work helping out on handbags?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, you can always look down and pick nothing up. There's no use being poor and seeming poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And your mother always said this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. Yes. No use being poor and seeming poor, always put a good face on outside. And when you'd be saying about windows she was say, I must have the windows right because more 
pass by than come in. We had to dress to the public, you know what I mean when I say that. Always give people a good impression. I think it pays don't you. Because if you go out untidy and you go in a shop people'll give you anything but if you're smart t
hey'll hesitate about pushing anything on you, they say, oh well she - she don't look as though she'll bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And this always stuck in your mind about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When you started at Lewis's what hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I had to be there for half past eight and we worked 'til eight o'clock at night and we got four shillings a week and our dinners.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you work Saturdays too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Wednesday they used to let you have - sometimes on a Wednesday, sometimes on a Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no. We didn't have any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505  holidays}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you think that this was a fair wage that you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, I was very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You thought it was good in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, well it looked a lot of money to me 'cos I'd never had money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you gave it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How much in the shilling did you say you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 A penny in the shilling. And I had a friend that worked there, Annie P
rendergast and we used to walk home, from Lewis's to Moston. Yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And your mother put it in the housekeeping did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well of course, yes, it had to go with the lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 Oh a
ll right, they thought I was a nice - they used to say - you know - sort of - I was all right - a good little girl they used to tell you, you know 'cos you were only little to them.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember your boss, how did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 There wa
s just one that - was awkward, one of the shop walkers was awkward, he used to say, oh you're always the last, in that department, they wanted to get you out of the departments but you see if you - I was in drapery. Well someone'd come in perhaps that was
 working at the shops near we had - we used to have stock collars if you - you won't remember - used to have little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 lace}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 collars like that, they called them stock collars 'cos they used to have them round there and perhaps somebody that was going to work'd come - you know, on a waitressing job or anything'd come in. Well perhaps it'd throw }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9075989\charrsid15489505 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 out with your money or whatever it were, you had to alter it again. And you daren't show an alteration on your slip. They used to say never show an alteration on a sli
p always make a new slip. Because it looked as though you were doing something you shouldn't do if you didn't have a clear slip.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you feel about Lewis's as employers, did you think they treated you fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, I was very happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You liked the work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Yes. But then - me father said it was a blind alley job and you must get - you know - sort of something and he thought we should have a - someone that could sew in the house and he got me to go to learn sewing. And I
 hated every minute that I had to be there. Yes I did. I couldn't sit still. I wanted to be on the go. I wanted to see something, I didn't want to sit down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you went to Lewis's first and then you went to sewing next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, because I couldn't g
o where there were machinery because I wasn't fourteen, quite fourteen. So that's why I went to Lewis's. Because you didn't have to pass a doctor or anything to go to Lewis's, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 suppose}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  you do now but you didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 to then. Well when you went to sewing y
ou'd to pass the doctor. So of course when you passed the doctor you were supposed to be all right. Anyway he only used to - they used to always tease you about it you know and the doctor used to just look you and ask - ask you your birth certificate, ask
 
your mother and father's name and how old you were and he used to say - let me see your tongue and you put your tongue out and then he'd say, turn round. You turn round, that's it, you'd passed. That's all you got for passing and you were frightened to de
ath to go into the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why did you dislike sewing so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I had to sit still and I couldn't sit still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What were the hours as swing, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well you had to be there for half past eight and you finished at six o'cloc
k. And an hour for your dinner. Half past twelve 'til half past one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember your wage there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Four shillings. Yes, and I didn't get me food there. But I was learning a trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you work Saturdays there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Saturday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 mornings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15601985 .}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Saturday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 'Til twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You never worked Sundays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No - oh, only one time. I went to work - when I'd been sewing there I went to be a finisher at a place in - called Mil
lers - they called Fellers in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Millers Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and it was Jewish. But I only stayed a month because you had to work on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have Saturday off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, but I wouldn't work Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When you were in the sewing trade how did the employer treat you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - you didn't see much of any bosses there you know, you just saw the foreman that's all, or the forelady and - ooh, he was an old grouch and he - he - he was called Mr Fisher - he was an old grouch and he used to - just be pressin
g and be chewing perhaps tobacco and spit and I used think, ooh I couldn't do with that. I used to come home and keep telling 'em sort of thing so at the finish I got out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you disliked that work intensely did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Definitely. Oh since the first world war? Well - I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  in 1920. Well the first world war -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You'd be at home then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Well - I was at the Lancashire Furnishing Company and I worked there for five years. I went to work - I went as a clerk there a
nd the war was on and so they made me in charge of the place. Well then I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 from there and after that I went to work at Afflex and Bowns, for sale times each year. Then I went - when that job was finished in 1928 I think it was I went to be a dem
onstrator for - cocoa first and then there was six started and there was two to be kept on and I was one of the ones that were kept on and it finished with the cotton strike in Bolton. And then eventually }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 Mazawattee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  amalgamated with this Typhoo and the different things and it was done a way with, you never see Mazzawatte advertised now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You've already told me you'd have preferred another job, you'd have liked to have been a teacher wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I would very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you were at Lewis'
s approximately six months and then you were sewing about one year and then after this you told me you went onto this friend of your mother's to work in the shop for her didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So about 1911 you would be working for the friend of your mother's as a shop assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
It was a little grocers shop and I used to go there. Well then after I'd finished there I went to - he failed, the man failed and I went to - Blakeys in Tarriff Street in the ladies bag and belt department. Well it was a
 warehouse, you didn't handle money. The traveler sent their orders in and you got the orders ready and we had occasional people come in but you weren't mixing much with the public. Well then I went to the Lancashire and I was there for five years 'til 19
23.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you feel there was a division of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Definitely. Yes. Well - I went after the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh before 1918. Well, yes, because they used to say oh he
's got a - he's got a posh job, you know, they used to say, oh he's got a posh job, he's nothing, you know, he's only such a thing, that's what they used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What would be the difference, who would have the posh job and who had the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well perhaps the bosses son'd have the posh job or the boss's nephew had the posh job. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 And the others were just the runabouts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
That was so in the Parsonage. And you used to get a little bit annoyed when you sort of saw them - they couldn't do the job, they'd pick your brains for it but they'd get the praise for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Some people say in those days there was a great division of interest between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well you would because - when all's said and done th
ey paid better for those that had been trained. If you could go and say you'd - passed such a thing, like today, if you've passed such a thing you get a better thought of than the one that doesn't pass. Or that hasn't passed. Now my daughter's had that ex
perience, she applied for a position -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Apart from the training do you think there was a division between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Bound to be because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How do you think it showed, in their living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - yes, it would show in their
 manner. And their living too and you would look up to the craftsman rather than look up - rather - rather than sort of to the labourer. 'Cos you thin, oh he's all right, you know, he can do it and many time they made a mistake but you weren't to notice t
hose mistakes, it was only you that could make mistakes if you were in the lower class. You know how I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You told me your father was a clerk and you feel that you were middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you thought your father came in the craftsman class did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - we thought that - you know we thought that we were just a little bit of a cut above - the ordinary - well, was satisfied with - to ; to sort of like the dustman and those sort of people that weren't educated enough. You did like 
to think that you were just that little bit above. And as I got older and since - of course I'm speaking now - I notice that - I was in charge of the shop and the people that came to work for me, I know very well that they're youth was very different than
 me own and I'm very proud in a sense that I had the parent that would sort of be - strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And gave you this good background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well - you knew that you had it to do so you didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you think that your ideas about life changed once you - got to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, but I - I was quite happy to be at work and I got on with the people that I was with and - that I had to meet and then we had our 
own - sometimes we would call on the way home at the baths because we'd take our - a bit of something, take sandwiches and we'd go to the baths and have a good swim. That'd take you 'til half past eight or nine o'clock, we'd be perhaps the last in the bat
h
s and get the hose pipe squirted on us to make us come out and then on our way home we - we - we'd dry as well as we could then on our way home we'd be able to call in the chip shop and have some chips, ha'porth of chips on paper and - it was a place on C
ollier Street that we used to call and - it used to have sand on the floor, oh we thought it was lovely, you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Tell me about your job when you were doing tailoring, tell me in your own words about the bosses and the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I had to do some - they got me to do some hand }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 buttonholing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 and they said I'd make a very good hand buttonholer. But it didn't grow quick enough for me. And I didn't mind felling the coat sleeves and - that sort of thing but - that they got you to do as an appren
tice, you'd to start on those sort of things and you're to go the messages over to the warehouse for anything. Well I wasn't a bad sewer but at the same time it irritated me to have to sit still. Yes. Yes. They wouldn't let me go on a machine so I didn't 
- I fancied going on a machine but they said I'd get me fingers in the - I was too - wanting to be too quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your father said Lewis's was a dead end job, was he very upset when you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 
 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, he was very annoyed and I got in - in a - I got a good hiding for leaving. But I'd left the job then and gone to another }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  before I dare go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you'd gone on to another sewing job hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I'd gone to Kay - I went Kay Lees and I didn't like it there so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What did you do at Kay Lees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Buttonholing - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  buttonholing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
And then from her you went to work for this friend of your mother's in a shop? You said you liked it here and you used to go to night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I used to go to night school so that I would sort of better myself. And what I'd lost in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 between}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  leaving school and going to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 Crooks's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  I took it that I must learn at night school and go on that way, both of my brothers went to night school, all of them did. Renshaw shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You went to work in Mrs Renshaw's shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Only just out of - to - and I learnt about weighing and business and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 everything}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 because she was a widow and she'd to go very carefully. It was when they used to bring a cup and they could get fourpennyworth of jam or - you know - or som
e pickles or that sort of thing, so you'd to be - very careful in your weighing and she taught me how to be - so that I could manage a shop, you know what I mean, make profit in a shop - and I was very interested in a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You liked it there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, and I liked a shop. Well then of course when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  my husband's mother had a shop, you see, so I've always liked shop. Yes. I like meeting people. And I like to - you know, sort of - well - when I was at - the U.C.P. in later years I us
ed to like to sort of be - nice with them. If they'd had - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 trouble}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 and that they used to tell you their trouble and so forth and you got to know little bits of other peoples lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And you always liked this about being a shop assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You stayed at home when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, I never left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I thought I should be - when I brought me money home I thought I should get a lot for it and I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You suddenly felt grown up and mature did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Yes, I thought I were keeping the house going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 On only four shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you change your attitude to your brothers and sisters at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well - in a way it did, I used to think the young one should do something for me and he didn't. I was 1 - we were all equal, there was no bosses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You thought you were a worker then did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you still go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, we always had to go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you take an interest in politics as you grew older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I did, I belonged to the Clayton Fighting 1000.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It was a - I had the
 card somewhere, I don't know - they called it the Fighting 1000 for the Conservatives. Oh yes, they called it the Fighting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 1000}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You followed your dad then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 Churchill I think - not - not - Churchman was the - the agent for up there - you see, he had a lot of property. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, I - I was in the - anything like with politics or anything that - I thought'd be interesting I was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So you were interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Well I was a Conservative but - yes, I'm still - all me life I've be
en a Conservative, no matter how the cat jumps I'd still be Conservative for the simple reason that I take it this way, of course you have your opinion, I take it this way, that they're wanting to build up and the others are letting everything go. That's 
the meaning in my estimation of conserve, try to gather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
You told me about how you spent your spare time as a child, did you still do the same things as you grew older or did you suddenly become grown up and do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, on Sunday nig
hts we had to stay in for quite a - until we were quite old, when we'd be seventeen and eighteen then we could go out and we had to be in for nine o'clock, the girls nine o'clock and the boys ten o'clock, so that they could take their girls home if they'd
 been with any girls, but we'd to be in at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents want to know who do you were with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. Show me your company and I'll tell you who you are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your mother and father said this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Bring them home and let's see who you - let us see who you're talking to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So they expected to meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Company and I'll tell you who you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And they expected to know where you'd gone and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. What was the picture - if you said, I've been t
o the pictures, you'd out with a boy and perhaps you hadn't been to the pictures. Have you been - where have you been? Been to the - and did you go to - me mad' say, did you go to the pictures? And what was on at the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You had loads of new friends now did you when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes, you - and you used to go to socials. Used to go to the socials like and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 At church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, and have a little bit of a dance now and again you know. And then of course we started going to the C
onservative club. Oh well, I'd known me husband from being a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did you have any special friends at this time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Where did you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well L -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Tell me all about your teenagers and all the mischief you got up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well I had a girl friend, Bertha Hicks and we used to - that was the one I used to go swimming with. We belonged to the swimming club. For Osmond Street baths. And she used to go to the Independent - Independent church up on - Oldham 
Road at the corner I think it was of Livesey Street, anyway, she used to belong to that club so she got me to go with her. So we used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When did you start going out with boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh well I must have started going out with boyfriends when I was
 about sixteen I had the excuse because they were our - our Eddie's friends you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You were obviously pretty, because you had lots of boyfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You could get the boys, you know, could go out with them and that Vincent -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Did your parents know you were going out with boys though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
No, not really, they used to shut their eyes to it for a start. Well anyway, this - that Vincent Robinson that I was telling you about, he used to be the Enoch in Happydrome and - he came one day, he chance
d it and came up to the house and me mother said, do you mean to tell me you're going out with that boy? So I said, well, he's all right and he goes to our church. She said, whether he goes to our church or not he's not my - he's not the type for you, he 
wears purple stockings and a purple tie. Purple socks and a purple - don't let him come to this door again. You see, it was when the men were starting wearing coloured socks and coloured ties and that you know. And she thought it was awful. Only }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  and white you know you had to have. Me ma was very sort of set in her ideas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 And she had very definite opinions about who you went out with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. She didn't like him. Anyway I went with him just the same. 'Til I got tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Do you remember as a child if anyone did anything wrong}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505  in}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  the district that people disapproved of, how did they show their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well to tell the truth I don't remember any great things at all at Moston because it was very quiet. The only thing I remember hearing 
about anyone doing anything bad was when they was a big funeral on Moston Lane and some friends of ours were called Howells and the wife - the mother - Mrs Howell was as the front door and someone got in at the back door while she was at the front and the
y took her jewellery and took her money, I always remember that because it was an awful thing, that's the only thing I can remember. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It was a really respectable neighbourhood was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh yes. Was really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 When you look back on your childhood and your early life just tell me your impressions of it generally, about your home and everything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
Well looking back at me life I really think that I - I had a very fair chance in life and a very - I had a very good mother and a good father 
because although he was strict he was good, and I had a good mother and we were a very happy family until we grew up, like my mother said, when someone else starts putting their knees under your table, that's when the - family starts to break up.
\par 
