 told me babies came from cabbages you know. Yes. And she brought me this and it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  a - a doll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
s head - a doll and it was in green crinkle paper and underneath it was I think was they'd put - they must have had crack - for it for a cracker or something on the table and I always used to think that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 babies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  were in cabbages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 You wouldn't be able to talk to your mother about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, we didn't and I was very heartbroken when my mother had that little girl because I didn't know, you know, I used 
to say, I said to my mother, I used to be with a girl and they said and oh didn't you know? I didn't know 'til the night before she was born that - they said, and didn't you know? I said, no, I didn't know. Her said, ooh I'd have known it if it'd have bee
n my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 But you didn't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No, I never dreamt of anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 This was the custom in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, they - so then when - I was talking to me - I was very upset and then afterwards I was talking to me mother a
nd I said, well as a matter of fact, I went to work and I was at Parsonage at the time and Miss Morrow was our - our forelady and I'd bunked the work and she said to me, what's the matter with you today? And - she came to me at me desk and I said, well I'
m
 upset. She said, what are you upset for? I said, well we've got a baby at our house. So she said, well that's nothing to be - for you to be upset at. So I said, oh but it is, I said, I wouldn't have cared it I - if I'd have known I said, but I'm sure the
 
others that I've come down with this afternoon - this morning, they think I'm crazy 'cos I didn't know. Thought I was slow. So she said, well I wouldn't think so, she said, because - when all's said and done you don't think about your own parents so you l
i
ke that. Anyway she said, you're not the Marion I know if you don't buy your mother something nice when you're going home. Well I think I told you I got very little spends and I'd saved one and sixpence because I was going - this boy that I was going with
 
had bought me a nice brush and comb in a case at the Christmas like with a bright lining, I thought it was wonderful. So I thought, well I'll have to buy him something. So I was going to buy him a one and sixpenny cane anyway when she said to me, you shou
l
d buy your mother something. Just take - I said, well what can I do, I haven't got a lot of money. So she said, well, take her a jar of cowsfoot jelly and some flowers home and your mother'll think a lot about it. So anyway when I got home me father said 
t
o me, I said, can I go up to see ma? So he said, yes, if you're in a different mood than you were this morning. So of course, I went up and I said how sorry I was and would she have these, and what could I do for her, and we both cried. She said, I was ve
r
y upset this morning because you wouldn't look at the baby, you wouldn't look at me. I just went in the room and I said, when I got home on the Sunday night like I had to wash up and I thought I'd finished washing up when I'd gone out to me tea I didn't t
hing I was going to have the washing up. So me father said, there's going to be a baby here before morning. Well I cried. And me sister came home.
