\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 upset}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  about it. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, you told me that your brother was upset too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. The - so our Chris, when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  came - when she was twenty-one and she - we slept at hers she said, w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 hat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
 are you crying for? So I said, well we're having a baby here. So she said, well it's the same mother and father, we'll have to learn to love it. We'll have to learn to love it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Why were the boys upset though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
The boys didn't know until she was born and our Eddie knew and he'd gone off. He was disgusted. But the other two younger ones, they didn't know it w
as going to be - that we were going to have a baby. Anyway, when they heard the baby crying they said, ooh, what's that. It was about five o'clock in the morning. The baby was born at five o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was Eddie still disgusted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh e'
d gone - left home because he knew it was coming off. But the other two wee in bed and they heard this crying and they called out, Mrs Grady was on the landing and the doctor and that sort of thing and it was in and they said, ooh what's that? So we heard
, go to sleep. And they were big boys going to work you know. Go to sleep. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Your brother thought your mother was too old you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well our Eddie thought that me mother had had enough. He thought she'd had to struggle enough with all of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 So he was fond of her wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh he thought the world of his - of me mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Isn't it funny the way they were told about cabbages and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes. Oh yes, well we were all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 told}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 . I used to wonder - used to wonder but you never dreamt of your own mother having another baby 'cos, you know what I mean, you never thought of it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 , do}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  you now. And it was a shock to all of us. Anyway we had to get over it and I loved her and she - you know, sort of used to take her out, but my son -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 The baby didn't live long did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 -Two years. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 
But me sister wouldn't take her out for fear anyone might think it was hers, people were all sort of - you know, sort of people were very clever sometimes when they knew you were engaged and th
ey'd broken the engagement off you see, they all jumped to the conclusion that, oh it must be something like that if you were - weren't careful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 
So anyway ma had this little girl and - we loved her but she died you see. And our Edie came home from America,
 he went to Canada to a relative and he came home in the May but she'd been buried in the April so he was upset then you see. Anyway he went back again and he begged of me mother to let him take the boys. So he said, to me mother he said, they'll be war. 
A
nd every man in England'll have to go. Let; me take them with me. And she said, no, it's enough to have one wanderer without any more. Anyway you see me brother was killed. And then the other one went in the army, so it broke the family life up all togeth
er.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 This often happened that there was a baby late in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, well you see, I wouldn't get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  again, I thought, I'm having no more babies. Nothing, I never saw anyone that I fancied, I could have done, I could have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347939 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505  again but I wouldn't be bothered and I used to think to myself, yes, my mother had a baby at forty-six, there's no one coming practicing on me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 How did you feel about not being told about babies, do you think it was a good thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Well I do, I think it left you a child whereas today they're all women before they're young. Don't you think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Who told you they came out of cabbages though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Oh our Madge and Chris always told -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Not your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8455755\charrsid15489505 mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 No. Me mother never discussed it with you. B
ut our Madge and Chris - then you see when my sister had a baby I knew, that - you know what I mean, you got to know through hearing 'em talking, but - this - it was - I'll always think about it, it had like a - a fancy piece of wig on you know and this -
 you see, this fancy piece of hair on like and it was a lovely face in this cabbage and it just had like a pink top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 This is the doll you're talking about? How about your father how did he feel, was he bitter about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Me - me father - no he never - they never bothered with one another for all those years and my father never put pen to paper to him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Was he not offended when your brother left home because the baby was on the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5271276 MI  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 Yes, yes, he was. But he - they never - as I tell you they
 never mixed - never met one another for - Eddie came home and then they got friends like and then he went back. He went back to America and he got in on the - twentieth of July and war was declared on the fourth of August. And - so of course he was in Am
e
rica then, he didn't have to come back. And me father and him, they never corresponded or anything. Me mother would but me father didn't. So then - the next thing was of course - Eddie used to send me mother money, when pa retired. Well then, when Eddie -
 Eddie had sent me father the money, when me mother died he sent it just the same. Of course me father had to write then to thank him for it you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12270389\charrsid15489505 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7819457 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15356496\charrsid15489505 It's a pity for it break up like that after being such a happy home?
